Sunpower outperformed in 2020 with record PATMI of RMB377.0 millionExceeded performance targets in FY2020- Revenue rose 12.6% YoY to record RMB4 058.8 million while PATMI hits another record of RMB377.0 million- Results exceeded convertible bond performance target of RMB370 million in 2020- Underlying operating cashflow grew 17.4% YoY to RMB535.9 million- Proposed first and final ordinary dividend of S$0.003 per share for FY2020  the 11th consecutive year of dividends. Raised by 20% from S$0.0025 per share in FY2019GI business contributions grew in importance to the Group  despite the pandemic- GI revenue rose 15.6% YoY to RMB1 335.2 million in FY2020- GI EBITDA rose 12.9% YoY to RMB488.7 million in FY2020- GI growth to continue to be driven by ramp-up of existing plants  supply area coverage  customer base expansion and capacity expansion of certain existing plants  as well as the addition of more potential earnings-accretive projectsM&S business maintained stable full-year uptrend- M&S revenue was RMB2 723.6 million in FY2020- Order book was RMB2.9 billion as at end-January 2021  compared to RMB2.8 billion as at end-September 2020Announcement links:SGX Announcementhttps://links.sgx.com/FileOpen/20544509_Announcement.4Q2020Results.ashx?App=Announcement&FileID=649735Presentationhttps://links.sgx.com/FileOpen/20544508_Announcement.InvestorPresentation.ashx?App=Announcement&FileID=649737Press releasehttps://links.sgx.com/FileOpen/20544505_Announcement.4Q2020PressRelease.ashx?App=Announcement&FileID=649736
